  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 180°C. Add the cashew nuts to a baking tray and roast until golden and fragrant, then remove and leave to cool."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the dressing. Zest the lime and then cut it in half ready for juicing. Deseed and finely chop the chilli (if you fancy a bit more spice you can add extra). Roughly chop the mango and add it to a high-speed blender with the lime juice, cumin, olive oil and water. Blitz until smooth, then season with salt and black pepper. Finally, stir through the lime zest and chopped chilli."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the rice following pack instructions. Halve the cherry tomatoes, then peel the carrots and cut them into fine matchsticks. Pick the Thai basil leaves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the rice to a large bowl along with the prawns, tomatoes, carrots, Thai basil, coconut chips and roasted cashews. Pour over the dressing, toss well to coat and serve."
    }
  ],
